<plot>An entry in the "Musical Parade" featurettes from Paramount, production number FF5-6. Gangsters force night club owner Mike to sell out, thereby throwing singer Mary Daley and publicity man Nat Foster out of work, and also preventing Mike from financing Nat's play. Mike tries to stop the sale and is killed by the gangsters. But, every cloud has a silver line (except for Mike), and it is discovered that he left a provision in his will for Nat's show to be produced and for Mary to star in it. The dance team of Harris &amp; Shore is also along.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?219091</url></doc>
